The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 TIL has registered a 52 per cent rise in profit at Rs 28.83 crore for the year ended March 31, 2007 against Rs 18.85 crore previous year. The consolidated total income of the company has increased 41 per cent to Rs 773.12 crore from Rs 548.90 crore last year. The earnings per share rose 59 per cent. The board of directors has recommended a dividend of Rs 3 per share.

 Havells India has recorded a 54 per cent rise in net revenues at Rs 1,547 crore in 2006-07 against Rs 1,003 crore in the previous year. Profit after tax was up 62 per cent at Rs 102 crore from Rs 63 crore. Net revenue for the fourth quarter ended March 31, 2007 was up 47 per cent at Rs 440 crore while net profit increased 57 per cent to Rs 29 crore. The company has announced a final dividend of 50 per cent for 2006-07.

 Ess Dee Aluminium has reported a 297 per cent jump in profit after tax at Rs 37.3 crore for the quarter ended March 31, 2007 against Rs 9.4 crore in the year-ago period. Income from operations increased 169 per cent to Rs 170.6 crore from Rs 63.5 crore. 

 JK Cement has posted a 448 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 178.6 crore for the year ended March 31, 2007 against Rs 32.6 crore last year. The profit before tax increased 421 per cent to Rs 272 crore from Rs 52.2 crore. Net turn-over rose 41 per cent to Rs 1,2333 crore. 

 Adidas has launched Adidas Retail University, a training programme for front end sales staff on customer service, selling skills, visual merchandising, and shop management.

 Cadila Healthcare has introduced an anti-obesity drug, Slimona. The drug will be used to treat obese patients with associated risk factors, such as Type II Diabetes or Dyslipidemia. The drug is priced at Rs 5.50 per tablet.

 Titan Nebula has introduced the Trousseau Collection of 18 karat gold watches. The range is priced between Rs 40, 000 and Rs 50,000.

